Package vehicles

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AGC
    EN The AGC is an AGV derived class, used to identify an Automatic Guided Cart, a vehicle.
    AGV
    EN The AGV class (Automatic Guided Vehicle) is an abstract class referring to a vehicle in the distribution center space used for transportation of Transportable objects.
    TowingVehicle
    EN The TowingVehicle is an AGV derived class, a vehicle that does not transport any package or products, but a transport cart.
    TransportCart
    PT The TransportCart class is meant to be used alongside the TowingVehicle, as in it serves an appendage.
    ULC
    EN The ULC is an AGV derived class, used to identify an Unit Load Carrier, a vehicle.
